(2,5) = 1
n^5 = 2k + n
2k+n \equiv n \pmod 5 \implies 2k \equiv 0 \pmod 5 \implies k \equiv 0 \pmod 5
k = 5m
n^5 = 2(5m) + n  = 10m +n
n^5 \equiv n \pmod {10}
\rm{(QED)}
